like, um...

07:01.622 --> 07:04.592
of course, uh,
Glasses McLabcoat

07:04.625 --> 07:07.194
and, uh, the...

07:08.662 --> 07:10.230
-...the-the girl who would kick,
-Oh.

07:10.263 --> 07:12.432
-kick everyone, I miss her.
-Yeah.

07:12.466 --> 07:14.802
Oh, and Sydney.
Don't forget Sydney.

07:14.835 --> 07:17.437
-I had forgotten Sydney, yes.
-Oh, it...

07:17.471 --> 07:19.473
oh, what happened to her
was so sad.

07:19.507 --> 07:22.643
Very sad. Uh...

07:22.676 --> 07:25.245
: What was it
that happened to her again?

07:25.278 --> 07:27.314
-The betrayal.
-She was betrayed.

07:27.347 --> 07:29.349
-After the fight with Farouk,
-Mm.

07:29.382 --> 07:31.418
when David...

07:31.451 --> 07:33.153
-The Turn.
-...turned.

07:33.186 --> 07:34.622
The Turn. Uh...

07:34.655 --> 07:37.090
there was a great battle with...

07:37.124 --> 07:38.659
what's his face.

07:38.692 --> 07:40.460
-Fa... Farouk.
-Farouk. Farouk.

07:40.494 --> 07:43.263
Uh, very soothing voice,
I found. Very hypnotic.

07:43.296 --> 07:44.665
Mmm.

07:47.367 --> 07:49.469
I remember helping him.

07:52.005 --> 07:54.875
Yes, I... I do, too.

07:59.680 --> 08:01.014
Hmm.

08:02.883 --> 08:06.219
Why did he turn again,
this David person?

08:08.889 --> 08:12.492
Because she showed him
his future.

08:27.775 --> 08:30.310
No.

08:30.343 --> 08:33.714
-No, no, no, no.

08:42.255 --> 08:44.257
SYD:
We need to talk.

08:45.759 --> 08:47.160
Sure.

08:47.194 --> 08:49.429
Let me just finish killing
this asshole.

08:52.099 --> 08:55.335
You haven't had a lot of
girlfriends, or you'd know--

08:55.368 --> 08:58.572
when a woman wants to talk,
you talk.

09:01.208 --> 09:03.410
Could you maybe not point
that thing at me?

09:03.443 --> 09:06.046
You read the stories.

09:06.079 --> 09:09.516
The women who marry serial
killers and have six kids--

09:09.549 --> 09:12.185
meanwhile, he's driving
around Portland every night

09:12.219 --> 09:14.722
with a van full of duct tape.

09:15.756 --> 09:17.691
What?

09:17.725 --> 09:19.526
They have to know.

09:19.559 --> 09:22.596
Right? The wives, deep down.

09:22.630 --> 09:26.566
At least a feeling,
something's wrong.

09:26.600 --> 09:30.570
I know, with you. Now.

09:30.604 --> 09:32.472
Syd, I'm the good guy.

09:32.505 --> 09:34.541
He's the monster.

09:34.574 --> 09:36.076
No.

09:38.445 --> 09:40.413
You're not that.

09:40.447 --> 09:43.150
A good guy?

09:43.183 --> 09:45.552
I thought so for a long time.

09:45.585 --> 09:48.789
And then I saw
the things you hide.

09:52.626 --> 09:55.328
And it hit me.

09:55.362 --> 09:57.931
What if you're not the hero?

09:57.965 --> 10:00.400
What if you're
just another villain?

10:00.433 --> 10:02.836
The real villain.

10:05.272 --> 10:07.240
Why? 'Cause...

10:07.274 --> 10:09.843
because I didn't tell you
the whole truth?

10:09.877 --> 10:12.112
Because I

10:14.114 --> 10:16.416
-He kills people.
-You...

10:16.449 --> 10:18.986
kill people.

10:19.019 --> 10:21.454
Dozens at Division 3 last year.

10:21.488 --> 10:23.590
No. That was him.

10:23.623 --> 10:25.859
He had c-control.

10:25.893 --> 10:28.095
The Son of Sam had a dog
who gave him commands,

10:28.128 --> 10:32.632
but every time he pulled the
trigger, he pulled the trigger.

10:36.169 --> 10:38.005
Seriously,
why are you doing this?

10:38.038 --> 10:40.207
I... know.

10:40.240 --> 10:42.142
That's the thing.

10:42.175 --> 10:43.811
I've seen your true face.

10:43.844 --> 10:46.847
You hid it so well.

10:50.183 --> 10:52.152
I love you.

10:52.185 --> 10:54.654
Maybe.

10:54.688 --> 10:56.656
But here's what matters more.

10:56.690 --> 10:59.059
You lie to me.

10:59.092 --> 11:01.995
You leave me.

11:02.029 --> 11:04.364
-You keep secrets.
-No.

11:07.600 --> 11:10.503
You're doing it right now.

11:10.537 --> 11:13.640
Unless maybe you don't know
the difference-- truth, lie.

11:13.673 --> 11:15.175
Maybe...

11:15.208 --> 11:17.878
it's not even your fault.

11:17.911 --> 11:22.315
He was in your head for so long,
poisoning every thought.

11:22.349 --> 11:25.352
Are you okay? Y-Your neck,
that's a lot of blood.

11:25.385 --> 11:27.154
It's not mine.

11:27.187 --> 11:30.523
Listen to me,
I know it's been hard...

11:30.557 --> 11:32.726
I saw what you did to Oliver.

11:32.760 --> 11:35.395
To the soldiers at Division 3.

11:35.428 --> 11:37.765
I saw the look on your face.

11:37.798 --> 11:40.067
You liked it.

11:40.100 --> 11:42.202
No, I did what I had to.

11:42.235 --> 11:44.271
You tortured Oliver.

11:44.304 --> 11:46.173
You were beating him to death.

11:46.206 --> 11:48.809
That's not a love story.

11:53.046 --> 11:54.848
*

11:54.882 --> 11:56.249
Wait, I...

11:56.283 --> 11:58.685
I'm just, we're just,
this is...

11:58.718 --> 12:01.621
We're just doing
what you said. You.

12:01.654 --> 12:03.056
This is war. We're in a war.

12:03.090 --> 12:04.291
What am I willing to do?

12:04.324 --> 12:06.760
How far am I willing to go?

12:06.794 --> 12:08.695
-I know I said that, but...
-And that's all I'm doing.

12:08.728 --> 12:10.730
That is all I am doing--
what you said.

12:10.764 --> 12:12.432
No. No.

12:12.465 --> 12:13.901
Baby, please.

12:13.934 --> 12:15.969
What happened
to "God loves the sinners best"?

12:22.109 --> 12:24.177
:
It won't work.

12:25.245 --> 12:27.280
We're all powerless now.

12:27.314 --> 12:29.950
Goddamn it, put the gun down
and talk to me.

12:29.983 --> 12:31.651
He's gonna... it's gonna
wear off, and then he'll be--

12:31.684 --> 12:33.086
you heard them-- unstoppable.

12:33.120 --> 12:36.156
And, look, I'm sorry
if you have abandonment issues.

12:36.189 --> 12:38.625
And I was taken away by you,
if we're being--

12:38.658 --> 12:40.227
if we're laying all our cards
out on the table,

12:40.260 --> 12:41.728
so think about that.
I didn't leave.

12:41.761 --> 12:43.263
You kidnapped me
from the future.

12:43.296 --> 12:45.632
Did you ever ask why?
Why would I do that?

12:45.665 --> 12:47.734
Reach out from the future?

12:47.767 --> 12:49.469
Why ask you to help Farouk
find his body?

12:49.502 --> 12:51.338
Because of the world--
the end of the world?

12:51.371 --> 12:53.974
And who does that,
end the world

12:54.007 --> 12:56.143
Otherwise, why would I ask you
to save him?

12:56.176 --> 12:59.079
I don't know. You wouldn't,
you didn't tell me.

12:59.112 --> 13:02.749
-It's you.

13:02.782 --> 13:05.785
You're the one who destroys
everything, who ends the world.

13:12.225 --> 13:14.027
No.

13:14.061 --> 13:15.662
It never occurred to you

13:15.695 --> 13:18.465
that you're the problem,
not the solution.

13:18.498 --> 13:22.302
-H-How could you even...
-He showed me-- Farouk.

13:22.335 --> 13:24.671
He went to see her, too--
me, in the future--

13:24.704 --> 13:26.773
after you quit.

13:26.806 --> 13:29.176
See, in her timeline,
you killed Farouk,

13:29.209 --> 13:31.478
and then there was no one
powerful enough to stop you

13:31.511 --> 13:33.446
-when you turned.
-When I...

13:33.480 --> 13:37.050
So she tricked you
into helping him-- your enemy--

13:37.084 --> 13:38.818
so that he could stop you

13:38.852 --> 13:41.254
when you showed us
who you really are.

13:45.392 --> 13:48.528
I know.

13:48.561 --> 13:51.498
It's cold to do that to someone
that you used to love.

13:51.531 --> 13:53.967
Used to?

13:54.001 --> 13:57.304
Baby, please, I'm right here.

13:57.337 --> 14:02.109
Your man. Don't you trust me?

14:11.118 --> 14:14.121
Maybe I just trust myself more.

14:17.090 --> 14:19.526
No. He's...

14:19.559 --> 14:22.562
You're being tricked.
Syd, please.

14:25.232 --> 14:29.069
Syd, please.

14:29.102 --> 14:31.071
You know me.

14:31.104 --> 14:33.240
Yeah, I do.

14:33.273 --> 14:35.708
And guess what?
You're not the hero.

14:35.742 --> 14:38.045
Then who is?

14:40.647 --> 14:42.282
Me.

14:49.656 --> 14:51.858
NARRATOR : A delusion
starts like any other idea,

14:51.891 --> 14:53.961
as an egg.

14:53.994 --> 14:55.395
Identical on the outside,

14:55.428 --> 14:58.298
perfectly formed.

14:58.331 --> 15:01.868
From the shell, you'd never
know anything was wrong.

15:01.901 --> 15:03.470
A delusion starts

